==The vowel ㅓ (''eo'')==
{{:Korean/stroke order and sound
| jamo=ㅓ (''eo'')
| image=ㅓ (eo) stroke order.png
| sound=Open-mid back unrounded vowel.ogg}}
The next of the vowels to learn is ㅓ (''eo''):

{|
|- align=center
| style="font-size:75%" | [[w:Hangul#Jamo|Letter (''jamo'')]]:
| style="font-size:200%;border:3px solid;padding:10px 10px 10px 10px;" | ㅓ
|- align=center style="font-size:75%"
| [[w:Revised Romanization of Korean|Romanization]]:
| ''eo''
|- align=center style="font-size:75%"
| [[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|Pronunciation]]:
| [[w:Open-mid back unrounded vowel|[ʌ]]]
|}

The vowel ㅓ is pronounced like [[w:Open-mid back unrounded vowel|the ''u'' in ''pl'''u'''s'']] ([[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]: [ ʌ ]) and [[w:Revised Romanization of Korean|transcribed as ''eo'']] (think "surg'''eo'''n"). Similar in appearance to ㅏ (''a''), the vowel ㅓ (''eo'') is taller than it is wide, so it is written next to the consonant.

