==The vowel ㅔ (''e'')==
{{:Korean/stroke order and sound
| jamo=ㅔ (''e'')
| image=ㅔ (e) stroke order.png
| sound=Close-mid front unrounded vowel.ogg}}
The next vowel to learn is the digraph ㅔ (''e''):

{|
|- align=center
| style="font-size:75%" | [[w:Hangul#Jamo|Letter (''jamo'')]]:
| style="font-size:200%;border:3px solid;padding:10px 10px 10px 10px;" | ㅔ
|- align=center style="font-size:75%"
| [[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|Pronunciation]]:
| [[w:Close-mid front unrounded vowel|[e]]]
|}

The appearance the vowel ㅔ shows that it was originally a [[w:Diphthong|diphthong]] of ㅓ (''eo'') and ㅣ (''i''). Today, it is pronounced like [[w:Close-mid front unrounded vowel|the ''e'' in the Australian pronunciation of word ''b'''e'''d'']] and [[w:Revised Romanization of Korean|transcribed as ''e'']].

