==The vowel ㅐ (''ae'')==
{{:Korean/stroke order and sound
| jamo=ㅐ (''ae'')
| image=ㅐ (ae) stroke order.png
| sound=Open-mid front unrounded vowel.ogg}}
The last vowel for this lesson is the digraph ㅐ (''ae''):

{|
|- align=center
| style="font-size:75%" | [[w:Hangul#Jamo|Letter (''jamo'')]]:
| style="font-size:200%;border:3px solid;padding:10px 10px 10px 10px;" | ㅐ
|- align=center style="font-size:75%"
| [[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|Pronunciation]]:
| [[w:Open-mid front unrounded vowel|[ɛ]]]
|}

The appearance the vowel ㅐ shows that it was originally a [[w:Diphthong|diphthong]] of ㅏ (''a'') and ㅣ (''i''). Today, it is pronounced like [[w:Open-mid front unrounded vowel|the ''e'' in the American pronunciation of the English word ''b'''e'''d'']] and [[w:Revised Romanization of Korean|transcribed as ''ae'']].

