{{ingredient}} | [[Cookbook:Basic foodstuffs|Basic foodstuffs]] | [[Cookbook:Meat and poultry|Meat and poultry]] ---- '''Horse''' produce a meat that is sweet, tender, low in fat, and high in protein. Just like [[Cookbook:beef|beef]] and [[Cookbook:pork|pork]], in some societies there is a taboo regarding the consumption of horse meat.
Horse meat has about 40% less calories than even the leanest beef, while supplying 50% more protein and up to 30% more iron.{{fact}}
[[Category:Meat and poultry|Horse]]

